# ───────────────────────────── Dependencies ─────────────────────────────
node_modules/

# ──────────────────────────── Logs & OS cruft ───────────────────────────
*.log
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ──────────────── Local config (copy from config.example.txt) ────────────
# config.txt holds machine-local model/concurrency overrides. The tool falls
# back to sensible defaults when it is absent, so it is user-local, not committed.
config.txt

# ───────────── The source book PDF (≈44 MB, copyrighted) ─────────────
# The transcribed, hand-verified text under data/book/pages/ is the
# committed working source. The original PDF is NOT redistributed.
# See input/README.md for how to obtain it (needed only to re-run transcription).
input/*.pdf

# ───────── Generated / large / regenerable artifacts under data/ ─────────
# Regenerate: tiles via `ppt ocr`; quality via `ppt grade`; html & pdfs via `ppt render` / `ppt build-pdf`.
data/book/tiles/
data/logs/
data/quality/
data/html/
data/pdfs/

# ─────────────────────── Website (see website/.gitignore) ───────────────
website/node_modules/
website/dist/
# website/public/data/ is regenerated by `npm run sync-data`
website/public/data/

# ───────────────────────────── What IS committed ────────────────────────
# Everything else under data/ is committed on purpose — the website and CI
# build from it with zero pipeline runs:
#   data/book/pages/**                       transcribed source text (source of truth)
#   data/book/panch-pratikraman.full.md, data/book/ocr-manifest.json
#   data/corpus/pratikraman-structure.json   recitation tree (curated input)
#   data/corpus/canonical.json, vidhi.json   generated, committed for the website + CI
#   data/tradition-knowledge/*.md            injected knowledge base
#   data/glossary/*.json                     pos-labels + the three language glossaries
#   data/translations/**                     THE corpus the website renders
